	<TD CLASS="smalltext">29 March 2001, 11:22 GMT</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD CLASS="largetext"><B>More improvements to GuildMagic</B></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD><IMG SRC="images/shim.gif" HEIGHT="10"></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD CLASS="mediumtext">I've just uploaded a new bunch of changes. I've been working on the FAQ and some cosmetic improvements while Nan has been busy improving the way guild administrators can accept new members into their guilds. If you're a guild admin and someone has asked to join your guild you'll now see that you can select their <B>guild role</B> and <B>main/alt status</B> at the same time as choosing to <B>accept</B> or <B>decline</B> their application. In addition you'll see a list of the other characters that user has in your guild so you can more easily make your decision.
<P>
I'm keen to see GuildMagic become a more useful resource for guild officers and leaders. To that end I've openned up a <B>guild leadership</B> discussion chat board. It's passworded but guild admins can find the password on their 'My User' page (look for the animated <B>news</B> icon). This is experimental at the moment. We'll be watching where the discussion leads and possibly adding more boards to cover common areas of discussion.
<P>
Finally, there are more big changes on the horizon. The promised <B>Awards</B> functionality is nearing completion, <B>Guild Alliances</B> will follow shortly afterwards and Nan is now working on <B>Character Locations</B> so you'll be able to set the general or specific area where your characters are presently hunting.</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD><IMG SRC="images/shim.gif" HEIGHT="10"></TD>
</TR>
